TT 2152 "1349. Amicia and Hugo De Rune fled their homeland—A land devastated by war, rats, and the forces of the Inquisition, who sought to get their hands on the young boy and the unearthly power he inherited. Along the country lanes, they have found a little peace, with their mother, Beatrice and their companion Lucas, an apprentice alchemist. They are now discovering the County of Provence, where they hope to learn more about the Macula—the sickness that runs through Hugo's veins." LOADING__CHAPTER__1
TT 2153 "A tragic incident with some peasants compelled Amicia to kill again, while Hugo took refuge in a vision of an idyllic island which might hold a cure for the Macula. Caught by her victim's relatives, Amicia must save her own family in a brutal confrontation which leaves her traumatized. Now at the doorstep of the red city, all four are looking for Vaudin, Magister of the Order, whom Beatrice wishes to consult about Hugo's sickness." LOADING__CHAPTER__2
TT 2154 "On their way to meet Vaudin, the alchemist who will examine Hugo, Amicia and Lucas found a poor district of the red city where the inhabitants have been quarantined and decimated by the Bite. There, they faced mercenaries and thousands of rats emerging from the depths, both wreaking havoc. At his laboratory, Vaudin called Amicia a “Protector”, the title given by the Order to denote her relation to the Macula Carrier. Now it's time for the three of them to join Hugo." LOADING__CHAPTER__3
TT 2155 "Vaudin began to study Hugo's sickness, but his treatment led the boy to have a seizure. Amicia and Lucas went to search for calming herbs. They learned that the rats had started attacking some areas of the red city and fought against the Count's army, who'd begun a blind purge on the inhabitants in an attempt to contain the bite. Amicia plunged again into violence, which overwhelmed her and lead to their arrest. The duo is sentenced to die but Lucas reminds Amicia of her responsibilities and she pull herself together. They both escape, just in time to bring back the plants." LOADING__CHAPTER__4
TT 2156 "Vaudin thought Hugo wouldn't make it and persuaded Beatrice to leave for the headquarters of the Order in Marseille, where her son's devastating power might be contained. Amicia was against it but still helped Lucas to reach the harbour and Joseph, a boat captain who would take them aboard. Unconscious, Hugo released gigantic waves of rats, devouring the city. Vaudin died before Amicia managed to calm her brother down. The boy is horrified by what he did to this city he loved. The reunited family now heads towards Marseille." LOADING__CHAPTER__5
TT 2157 "Along the still waterways to Marseille, the De Rune's boat was ambushed by the mercenaries they had already faced in the red city. Amicia tried to free the ship, but the gang leader Arnaud badly injured her head before Hugo unleashed the rats on their attackers to save his sister. Remaining on the shore, the siblings decided to let the ship slide away, leaving behind their mother Beatrice and Lucas, who didn't want to leave his teacher. Amicia and Hugo now both search for the island of Hugo's dreams." LOADING__CHAPTER__6
TT 2158 "Hugo and Amicia have wandered alone into the county of Provence, looking for the boy's prophesized island. Hunted by the Count's troops, they made it through the labyrinth of an old quarry. Severely injured by Arnaud, Amicia grew weaker and weaker, forcing Hugo to open a path for them by using his evolving power over the rats. When the soldiers rushed after them, Hugo lost control of the horde which was flooding the place. An unexpected hand pulled Amicia away from death at the last second." LOADING__CHAPTER__7
TT 2159 "Arnaud saved Amicia from death and earned Hugo's trust. The old knight promised Hugo he'd ask a smuggler called Sophia to help them reach La Cuna, the island from the boy's dreams. Amicia is initially against Arnaud, who'd previously tried to kill her, but she learned of his story and the loss he endured because of the Count—A wanted man, Arnaud now wants to flee with the De Runes. In a hideout, Sophia, the smugglers' chief, agrees to sail with them if they recover her vessel, seized by the Count's soldiers. As the storm rages, the four of them finally leave for the island." LOADING__CHAPTER__8
TT 2160 "Amicia, Hugo, and Arnaud landed on the island of La Cuna in the midst of annual celebrations. During the Count's speech, Arnaud tried to get Hugo to call the rats and kill the lord, his sworn enemy. Amicia discovers that Arnaud saved her on the continent in exchange for Hugo's help killing the Count with his rats. Arnaud fights the Count anyway, but Amicia stops him before he does more damage and Arnaud is sent to jail. Emilie, the Countess, arrives and invites Hugo and Amicia to her wonderful palace, where she tells them more about the Child of Embers, the child-god she and the whole island worship." LOADING__CHAPTER__9
TT 2161 "In search of answers to Hugo's unexplained dreams, the siblings met Sophia again. At the heart of the island, they discovered a map based on the Order's symbol. It led them to a sanctuary, once owned by the college of alchemists. There, they secretly witnessed a pagan ritual led by the Count and his wife, who longed to become the parents of the Child of Embers. Amicia and Hugo also learned about the existence of a former Macula Carrier, Basilius, and his Protector, Aelia, who was taken away from the child and brought to a fort. The De Runes now follow the tracks of their predecessors, hoping for a way to save Hugo." LOADING__CHAPTER__10
TT 2162 "Amicia, Hugo, and Sophia reached the fort. There, slavers were sacrificing slaves in their own version of worship of the Child of Embers. Their leader, Milo, was planning to secure his place by the Child's throne and bring down the Count, but Hugo used his power to punish the fanatics, which led to tensions with Amicia. In the crypt of an antique chapel, she unveiled Aelia's legacy including the location of the former Carrier. After Sophia kills Milo to save the De Rune siblings, Hugo disobeys Amicia again, destroying the fort with his rats. The trio head back to the island map after Sophia puts them back in their place." LOADING__CHAPTER__11
TT 2163 "During their confrontation with Milo, Hugo swept away part of the island and its population. He's devastated to have again destroyed a place he adored. Under the island's map, the trio found an entrance to an underground temple. There, they discover the fate of the former Carrier and his Protector: Aelia failed to save Basilius. Feeling abandoned and alone, the boy died, unleashing the Justinian plague as he did so. Yet this shows Amicia the truth—That Hugo will live if Amicia stays by his side, and they live a peaceful life." LOADING__CHAPTER__12
TT 2164 "Beatrice and Lucas found Amicia and Hugo's tracks again. Reunited at the Count's palace, Amicia told her mother everything they had found out. Beatrice is proud and admits how wrong she was. But the Count betrayed Amicia to offer Hugo to his wife, which meant killing the rest of the family. In a brutal confrontation, Emilie executes Beatrice in front of Amicia. When Hugo wakes up to see the carnage, he unleashes the rats and devastates the Palace with Amicia by his side. Emilie is devoured in front of the Count, who swears to find them again." LOADING__CHAPTER__13
TT 2165 "Amicia is devastated by grief after her mother's death and Hugo is not himself anymore, overwhelmed by the Macula. With Lucas' help, they cross a massive underground rats' nest. Amicia gathered all her energy to protect her brother from the vicious influence of the Macula. Hugo slowly came back to life. He insisted on saving Arnaud, who was about to be hanged. They succeeded and eventually caught up with Sophia, before sailing away on her ship. They are now heading to the continent to find a home where Amicia, Hugo and Lucas could live the rest of their life." LOADING__CHAPTER__14
TT 2166 "While sailing to the continent after surviving the island, Hugo and Amicia dream about their future new life. But the Count, filled with grief and rage since Hugo and Amicia killed his wife, catches up with them and boards them with his war ship. Amicia and Arnaud fought the Count's men, but Amicia was hit and fell. Thinking his sister dead, Hugo attacked the Count, who seized him. The Count planned to use Hugo as the spearhead of his army of conquest. Cornered, Arnaud chooses to flee, jumping overboard with Amicia still unconscious." LOADING__CHAPTER__15
TT 2167 "Amicia, Arnaud, Lucas, and Sophia survived Sophia's shipwreck and tried to stop the Count. Arnaud, who once lost a child on a battlefield because of the Count, fights him in a duel. He sacrificed himself, offering Amicia the chance to finally kill him. But Hugo unleashed a massive cloud of Nebula that would allow the rats to spread unchecked everywhere. As they now know the boy is in Marseille, Amicia, Sophia and Lucas escape the rats that are devastating the city from within, and eventually arrive in front of the town's gate." LOADING__CHAPTER__16
TT 2168 "Amicia and Lucas managed to reach Hugo, who gave himself to the Macula and was on the brink of destroying everything. Hugo used the last spark of humanity within himself to convince his sister and Lucas to kill him before it's too late. Despite the pain, Amicia and Lucas have to take the tragic decision to end Hugo's suffering and save the world he loved." LOADING__CHAPTER__17
