TT 6838 "Lead the way then." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__605_ESCORT__220__M__1
TT 6839 "Mother..." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__040__M__1
TT 6840 "Mother!" VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__056__M__1
TT 6841 "It's fine, don't worry... How did you find us?" VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__080__M__1
TT 6842 "Yes, back in the sixth century. A child called Basilius. We found him... chained in an Order prison designed especially for him..." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__150__M__1
TT 6843 "... I think they panicked when he reached his last threshold. They took him away from his Protector. Locked him in there... to contain... what would happen next." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__156__M__1
TT 6844 "Yes... Mother, Magister Vaudin said Hugo is condemned, but this is what the Order believes, based on their mistake in the past with Basilius. If he'd had his Protector, like Hugo has us, I'm almost sure nothing would have happened..." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__180__M__1
TT 6845 "Think about it... During the last months on the road, the times when it was quiet, everything was just fine. He was fine." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__190__M__1
TT 6846 "Something tells me... that if we settle down somewhere safe, and live there as a family..." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__210__M__1
TT 6847 "It would stop getting worse." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__216__M__1
TT 6848 "Me? Now? But we were about to leave." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__240__M__1
TT 6849 "Fine. Take me to him." VO__AMICIA__CH12__RTC__610_A_BANQUET__300__M__1
